1. Create your own command-line address-book program using which you can browse, add, modify, delete or search for your contacts such as friends, family and colleagues and their information such as emails address and/or phone number. Details must be stored for later retrieval

Solution:

  1. Create a class with fields like google contacts
  2. Create a file storage using xml / json / pickle
  3. Store, read and search through a file


  Addition: Make it command line tool and sync with Google contacts


2. Implement the replace command. This command will replace one string with another in the list of files provided

Soltion:
  1. Read file, search and replace string using readline
  2. Create regex to replace all the occurance of string in file

  Addition: Make it more user friendly by making it command line tool which can replace string recursively
